I can't for the life of me figure out why anyone would invest in the
airline industry. Please, someone tell me a group companies facing more
serious problems than the legacy airline carriers (Delta, <PLACE country="US" form="NAM" gazref="IGDB:840" id="Pl-1" predicative="true" type="COUNTRY">US</PLACE> Airways,
Continental, <PLACE country="US" form="NAM" gazref="IGDB:840" id="Pl-2" predicative="true" type="COUNTRY">American</PLACE>, Northwestern, United). High fuel costs, insane
pension obligations, and a highly paid, specialized workforce. To this
